  "title": "Reuse as Acceleration",
  "concept": "When one actor can reuse partial work from another, completion speed depends on how much reusable material already exists—more foundation means less new work, compressing the time to finish.",
  "interactiveId": "353eede3-1149-40a9-b5f8-8438923adcf0",
  "sourcePieceId": "2aba2c5f-0a3e-4c61-a3e2-8dddfc7945e7",
  "publishedAt": 1777552463647,
  "voiceScore": 88,
  "qualityFlag": "low",
  "content": {
    "type": "html",
    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<title>Reuse as Acceleration</title>\n<style>\n  :root {\n    --bg: #faf7f1;\n    --fg: #1a1a1a;\n    --muted: #6b6b6b;\n    --line: #e5e0d6;\n    --original: #2563eb;\n    --reuse: #ea580c;\n  }\n  * { box-sizing: border-box; }\n  body {\n    font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", sans-serif;\n    margin: 0;\n    padding: 20px;\n    color: var(--fg);\n    background: var(--bg);\n    line-height: 1.5;\n  }\n  h2 {\n    font-size: 1.05rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    margin: 0 0 4px;\n  }\n  p.subhead {\n    margin: 0 0 20px;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .control {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 14px;\n    margin-bottom: 24px;\n  }\n  .control label {\n    font-weight: 500;\n    flex-shrink: 0;\n  }\n  .control input[type=range] {\n    flex: 1;\n    accent-color: var(--original);\n    min-width: 120px;\n  }\n  .control output {\n    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    min-width: 3ch;\n    text-align: right;\n  }\n  .work-view {\n    position: relative;\n    height: 180px;\n    margin: 24px 0;\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    padding: 20px;\n  }\n  .bar {\n    position: absolute;\n    height: 50px;\n    left: 20px;\n    right: 20px;\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    overflow: hidden;\n    background: var(--line);\n  }\n  .bar-original {\n    top: 30px;\n  }\n  .bar-second {\n    top: 100px;\n  }\n  .segment {\n    position: absolute;\n    top: 0;\n    height: 100%;\n    transition: width 250ms ease-out, left 250ms ease-out;\n  }\n  .segment-reused {\n    background: var(--original);\n    opacity: 0.4;\n    left: 0;\n  }\n  .segment-new {\n    background: var(--reuse);\n  }\n  .bar-label {\n    position: absolute;\n    left: 20px;\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.06em;\n  }\n  .label-original {\n    top: 12px;\n  }\n  .label-second {\n    top: 82px;\n  }\n  .reading {\n    margin: 18px 0 6px;\n    padding: 10px 14px;\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .reading strong {\n    font-weight: 600;\n  }\n  .metric {\n    display: block;\n    margin-bottom: 6px;\n  }\n  .metric:last-child {\n    margin-bottom: 0;\n  }\n  p.caption {\n    margin: 14px 0 0;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.875rem;\n  }\n  @media (max-width: 480px) {\n    .control {\n      flex-direction: column;\n      align-items: stretch;\n      gap: 8px;\n    }\n    .control output {\n      text-align: left;\n    }\n    .work-view {\n      height: 160px;\n    }\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h2>Drag to set how much work the first actor completed</h2>\n<p class=\"subhead\">The second actor reuses completed work. Watch how total new work shrinks as reusable material increases.</p>\n\n<div class=\"control\">\n  <label for=\"completed\">Completed:</label>\n  <input id=\"completed\" type=\"range\" min=\"0\" max=\"100\" value=\"0\" aria-describedby=\"completed-out\">\n  <output id=\"completed-out\" for=\"completed\">0</output><span>%</span>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"work-view\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  <span class=\"bar-label label-original\">First actor (original work)</span>\n  <div class=\"bar bar-original\">\n    <div class=\"segment\" id=\"originalSegment\" style=\"background: var(--original); left: 0; width: 0%;\"></div>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"bar-label label-second\">Second actor (with reuse)</span>\n  <div class=\"bar bar-second\">\n    <div class=\"segment segment-reused\" id=\"reusedSegment\"></div>\n    <div class=\"segment segment-new\" id=\"newSegment\"></div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"reading\">\n  <span class=\"metric\">Reusable work: <strong id=\"reusable\">0</strong> units</span>\n  <span class=\"metric\">New work required: <strong id=\"newWork\">100</strong> units</span>\n  <span class=\"metric\">Total for second actor: <strong id=\"total\">100</strong> units</span>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"caption\" id=\"caption\">With no completed work to reuse, the second actor must do the full task from scratch.</p>\n\n<script>\n  (function () {\n    var slider = document.getElementById('completed');\n    var completedOut = document.getElementById('completed-out');\n    var originalSegment = document.getElementById('originalSegment');\n    var reusedSegment = document.getElementById('reusedSegment');\n    var newSegment = document.getElementById('newSegment');\n    var reusable = document.getElementById('reusable');\n    var newWork = document.getElementById('newWork');\n    var total = document.getElementById('total');\n    var caption = document.getElementById('caption');\n\n    function update() {\n      var completed = +slider.value;\n      completedOut.textContent = completed;\n      \n      originalSegment.style.width = completed + '%';\n      \n      reusedSegment.style.width = completed + '%';\n      \n      var newWorkUnits = 100 - completed;\n      newSegment.style.left = completed + '%';\n      newSegment.style.width = newWorkUnits + '%';\n      \n      reusable.textContent = completed;\n      newWork.textContent = newWorkUnits;\n      total.textContent = newWorkUnits;\n      \n      if (completed === 0) {\n        caption.textContent = 'With no completed work to reuse, the second actor must do the full task from scratch.';\n      } else if (completed < 25) {\n        caption.textContent = 'A small amount of reusable work trims the new work slightly. The second actor still does most of the task.';\n      } else if (completed < 50) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Reuse cuts the required new work. The second actor does less than the first actor did.';\n      } else if (completed < 75) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Most of the work can be reused. New work shrinks to a fraction of the original effort.';\n      } else if (completed < 100) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Nearly all work is reusable. The second actor finishes quickly by doing only the remaining gap.';\n      } else {\n        caption.textContent = 'All work is reusable. The second actor completes the task with zero new effort.';\n      }\n    }\n\n    slider.addEventListener('input', update);\n    update();\n  })();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
